&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Sport &amp;amp; Spine Physical Therapy is a premier provider of physical therapy and sports medicine service serving Portsmouth, NH for over 20 years. As a PT-owned private practice, we are driven to provide highly individualized patient care that is centered on results. At Sport &amp;amp; Spine, we focus on relieving pain, improving movement, and restoring functioning. We also provide preventative healthcare and education to reduce a patient’s risk of re-injury.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We are looking for passionate and driven professionals who bring the best of themselves to everything they do. If you are ready to make a meaningful impact in a setting that supports clinical excellence, career growth, and teamwork, apply now!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Our Clinical Affiliation Program&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sport and Spine Physical Therapy is honored to partner with the nation’s top PT, PTA, OT and SLP programs and provide aspiring clinicians with a unique, hands-on learning experience where you will learn, grow and make a difference in the lives of our patients. &lt;em&gt;*Must be currently enrolled and attending school for Physical Therapy/Physical Therapy Assistance, Occupational Therapy, or Speech Therapy)*&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Through our partnership with Fusion, we offer students two rotation options to complement the classroom setting:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outpatient: make an impact on a patient population of all ages. Work side-by-side with your Clinical Instructor (CI), learning and treating a variety of conditions and diagnoses including arthritis, chronic pain, musculoskeletal, orthopedic, pre-post surgery, sports injuries, vestibular and balance, and women’s health.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Senior Therapy: make an impact and provide access to care to a geriatric population living in Assisted Living and Memory Care locations. Work side-by- side with your CI, learning and treating a variety of conditions and offering programs for activities of daily living, fall prevention, functional mobility, movement disorders, orthopedic injuries, vestibular and balance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Throughout your time with us, we encourage you to ask questions, engage with patients, and immerse yourself in the practical aspects of your field. Your CI is eager to share their knowledge and expertise. Our goal is to provide you a transformative and enriching experience so that you leave understanding what great patient care is and feeling inspired and ready to make a positive impact, wherever you may practice next.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have any questions or if your program is interested in setting up an affiliation partnership with us, please contact us Students@FusionPTPartners.com&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sport &amp;amp; Spine Physical Therapy is committed to serving our team members who serve our patients and our communities. We offer competitive compensation and benefits for our employees and a collaborative, positive culture committed to patient care.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;At Sport &amp;amp; Spine, we invest in a culture of inclusion and positivity and encourage all to apply to our open roles. You will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sport &amp;amp; Spine is a proud member of &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fusionptpartners.com/&quot;&gt;Fusion Physical Therapy Partners.

